parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down unexpectedly, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: smoke coming from the air vents
wiring harness wires rubbing through and shorting out
and the vehicle cutting off at any speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to shut down unexpectedly, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: unpredictable and unexpected shutdown of ignition
and the ignition switch breaking contact without driver action.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle's electrical system to malfunction, leading to stalling or shutdown.
The failure of the wiring harness can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to stalling or shutdown.
symptoms: Wiring harness wires rubbing through and shorting out
smoke coming from the air vents

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake line can cause brake fluid leakage, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal travels to the floor
brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the emergency brake cable can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: smoke coming out of the vehicle
flames shooting out through the hubcaps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the caliper can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: smoke coming out of the vehicle
flames shooting out through the hubcaps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to address recall issues with rear brake lines and hood latch can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: but failure to address recall issues can lead to brake line failure

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Failure to Receive Replacement Jack under Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to receive a replacement jack under recall can leave the vehicle owner without a safe and reliable means of lifting the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries during maintenance or repairs.
symptoms: Vehicle owner receives recall notice but does not receive replacement jack
multiple calls to manufacturer or compliance manager without resolution
extended wait times for replacement part.
